The council states the benefits are;

- Reduction in North-South journey times;
Likelihood is that traffic will increase to circumvent toll roads. 

- Delivery of several housing and employment sites;
Proposed 24,000 to be built on a flood plain which is green belt and has significant wildlife and recreational value. 

- Reduction in traffic using town centre;
No conclusive evidence to support. 

- Reductions in the air quality and noise impacts in town centre; 
No conclusive evidence to support.

We seek a national policy for treatment of eating disorders:

Mandatory protocols in compliance with evidence-based practices (NICE 1.3);
Expeditious timeframes for assessment/referral/treatment;

Mandate allowing families to participate in planning for treatment, therapy, and discharge;

Minimum discharge standard of 100% weight-for-height based on personal growth charts;

Stipulation for staff training on ED behaviors and co-morbids;

Training for school personnel in basic assessment criteria (NICE 1.2)
